title: Album Page, "Dutch Farm House / Walk from Enkhuigen [sic] to Hoorn", August 22, 1887
medium: Graphite on cream paperboard tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, at top right, (inscribed in circle): 21; 23; at bottom right: Dutch farm house / walk from Enkhuizen to Hoorn / Aug 22nd, 1887
description: Vertical sheet torn with bottom half missing, leaving a rough bottom edge.  Depicted in center of sheet is a large timber-frame house with a chimney.  The house consists of three stories at one corner - the elevation is articulated by projecting stringcourses and terminates in a 'trapgevel' façade.  Adjacent at the ground level are two windows, one with a shutter hanging askew from its hinge.  At this corner of the house, one section up to the second story has been removed to create a round-arched entrance.

tombstone.epitaph:
Album Page, "Dutch Farm House / Walk from Enkhuigen [sic] to Hoorn", August 22, 1887.
August 22, 1887. Graphite on cream paperboard tipped into binding with fabric. Gift of Mrs. William Greenough. 1943-51-103.
